-- U.S. Food-Stamp Use at Record 46.68 Million in July, USDA Says
-- B y   A l a n   B j e r g a
-- 2012-10-05T21:21:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-05/u-s-food-stamp-use-at-record-46-68-million-in-july-usda-says.html
Food stamps went to a record 46.68
million Americans in July, the U.S. Department of Agriculture
said today. The figure is up from 46.67 million in June and 2.9
percent higher than in July 2011, the department said today in a
statement on its website.  Spending on the program totaled $6.26 billion in July, also
the highest ever.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alan Bjerga at 
 abjerga@bloomberg.net  